        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 10:27PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1027 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Garden City, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
